<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 7:19AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Coal
and west central Atoka Counties through 745 AM CDT...
At 718 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Lehigh, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Atoka, Stringtown, Tushka, Atoka Reservoir and Boggy Depot Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
